parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Bendix 10 ABS brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The ABS light is on
the brake pedal feels stiff or hard to press
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the brake pedal travels to the floor
the vehicle hesitates or won't move when the brake is applied
a loud humming noise is heard from the front
the brake fluid is contaminated with petroleum.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seatbelt buckle can cause the seatbelt to become unbuckled while driving, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seatbelt buckle will not stay buckled
the inside of the plastic buckle comes out
the buckle fails to latch properly
the buckle becomes stuck
the seatbelt will not extend from the panel
the seatbelt will not unbuckle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seatbelt anchorage can cause the seatbelt to become detached while driving, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seatbelt anchorage comes loose
the seatbelt hook/floor anchor fails
the seatbelt falls off the anchor
the seatbelt becomes unhooked from the floor anchor
the seatbelt anchorage releases when the belt is in use.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel rail leaks can cause fuel to spill onto the engine compartment, spark plugs, and other hot components, leading to a high risk of fire, engine damage, and potentially life-threatening accidents.
symptoms: Strong smell of gasoline
fuel fumes filling the interior compartment
gas leaking onto the valve cover
spark plugs
and engine block
fuel rail separation
U-tube connection leaks
O-ring failures
and injector leaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Ultradrive transmission can cause the vehicle to lock in a specific gear, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission shifts weirdly
the vehicle locks in second gear
the transmission fails to shift into gear
the vehicle jumps into different gears and jerks
the transmission slips
the vehicle has difficulty shifting out of first gear
the vehicle shuts down completely
the vehicle will not go faster than 30-40mph.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission solenoid body can cause the transmission to lock in a specific gear, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission solenoid body locks the transmission in drive/2/1 range
the transmission cannot be shifted to neutral
reverse
or park without a great amount of force
disconnecting the battery resets the controls and allows the gears to be changed normally for a short period.
